## Implementation

- File: shell script `test/test_integration_restart.sh` or OCaml integration test
- Steps:
  1. Start daemon (clawq service start)
  2. Wait for health endpoint to respond
  3. POST test message to /chat endpoint, capture session_key
  4. Verify message in SQLite messages table
  5. Run `clawq service signal-restart`
  6. Poll health endpoint until responsive (max 30s)
  7. Verify session history still present in DB for session_key
  8. POST another message, verify history context used (response refers to prior exchange)
  9. Cleanup: clawq service stop

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Full restart cycle completes without manual intervention
- [ ] History persists across restart (DB query confirms rows)
- [ ] Post-restart message uses prior context (agent references earlier exchange)
- [ ] Daemon PID unchanged after signal-restart (same PID in daemon.pid before and after)
- [ ] At least one drain warning message is delivered to an active session during drain sequence
- [ ] Test can run in CI (no interactive input, fixed timeouts)
